@218 = ~Burning Hands (Alteration)
Level: 1
Sphere: elemental (fire)
Range: 2 meters
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 60 degree arc
Saving Throw: 1/2

When the preacher of flames casts this spell, a jet of searing flame shoots from his fingertips. His hands must be held so as to send forth a fanlike sheet of flames: the preacher's thumbs must touch each other and fingers must be spread. The burning hands send out flame jets of 1.5 meters length in a horizontal arc of about 60 degrees in front of the preacher. Any creature in the area of the flames suffers 1d4 hit points of damage, plus 2 points for each level of the spellcaster, to a maximum of 1d4 + 20 points of fire damage. Those successfully saving vs. spell receive half damage.~
